Three files created:

- **`docs/architecture/v1-sectioning-and-priorities.md`** — canonical version sectioning reference using v1/v1.1/v1.2/v2 language. Defines what ships in each version, which packages are in scope, per-version success criteria, and which products each version unblocks. Replaces P0/P10 priority language throughout.

- **`docs/workflows/v1-workflow-backlog.md`** — ordered backlog of seven workflows (WF-1 through WF-7) with dependency graph, per-workflow steps, acceptance criteria, PR scope, execution order table, and a "first workflows to write next" section. Ends with `V1_WORKFLOW_BACKLOG_READY`.

- **`docs/workflows/weekend-delivery-plan.md`** — concrete Saturday/Sunday timeline with product-specific adoption paths for Sage, MSD, and NightCTO. Each product gets a minimum viable assembly code sketch, a list of what stays in the product repo, and a gating map through v1.1 and v1.2. Includes risk flags and Monday follow-on work.
